    <Placemark>
      <name>5. osm_way_230042909</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>Warning:</b> INTERNAL REVIEW ONLY. OpenStreetMap footprint candidate, not official EMS damage. VLM before/after output is a triage aid only; absence/presence here is not confirmation.<br/><b>VLM:</b> possible_major_damage confidence 0.45<br/><b>Evidence:</b> Within the OSM footprint outline, the pre-event image shows a clearly defined building structure with a discernible roof. In the post-event image, the same footprint area shows a lighter-toned, less defined rectangular mass that appears consistent with a partially collapsed structure or debris field rather than an intact roofed building. The change is visible but the post-event scene&#x27;s heavy haze/low contrast limits confidence.<br/><b>Uncertainty:</b> Post-event chip has poor contrast and apparent atmospheric haze/smoke, obscuring fine structural detail. The lighter patch within the footprint is consistent with collapse/debris but could also reflect a damaged but still-standing roof under poor imaging conditions. Insufficient resolution and contrast to confirm major damage versus partial/minor damage.<br/><b>Google Maps:</b> <a href='https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp;query=10.431210625,-66.964767225'>open</a>]]></description>
      <Point><coordinates>-66.964767225,10.431210625,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>
    <Placemark>
      <name>6. osm_way_233926033</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>Warning:</b> INTERNAL REVIEW ONLY. OpenStreetMap footprint candidate, not official EMS damage. VLM before/after output is a triage aid only; absence/presence here is not confirmation.<br/><b>VLM:</b> possible_major_damage confidence 0.45<br/><b>Evidence:</b> In the before chip, a clear multi-story apartment building with visible roof structure, walls, and defined footprint occupies the candidate outline. In the after chip, the same footprint area shows a darker, uniform, flattened surface with no discernible roof, walls, or height signature — consistent with collapse or severe structural loss. Surrounding context (vehicles, adjacent structures) is visible in both, but the after scene is heavily pixelated.<br/><b>Uncertainty:</b> After image is severely degraded in resolution and sharpness, so although the building&#x27;s roof and walls are no longer visible, I cannot distinguish between complete destruction, partial collapse with rubble spread, or a low-relief remnant under poor imagery. Confidence is therefore limited.<br/><b>Google Maps:</b> <a href='https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp;query=10.434816399999999,-66.9698764'>open</a>]]></description>
      <Point><coordinates>-66.9698764,10.434816399999999,0</coordinates></Point>
    </Placemark>
    <Placemark>
      <name>7. osm_way_279914444</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>Warning:</b> INTERNAL REVIEW ONLY. OpenStreetMap footprint candidate, not official EMS damage. VLM before/after output is a triage aid only; absence/presence here is not confirmation.<br/><b>VLM:</b> possible_major_damage confidence 0.45<br/><b>Evidence:</b> In the before image, a clearly defined elongated building with a green/vegetated roof is visible within the OSM footprint. In the after image, the distinct building structure is no longer discernible within the same footprint area, replaced by a uniform brownish-grey surface texture that could indicate rubble, debris, or collapsed structure. No clear building roof or walls are visible post-event.<br/><b>Uncertainty:</b> The after image has substantially lower resolution and appears blurry with possible cloud artifacts, making it difficult to definitively confirm building destruction versus just poor image capture. While the absence of a visible building structure in the after image is notable, the degraded post-event image quality prevents high-confidence damage classification. A human reviewer with access to higher-resolution post-event imagery would be needed to confirm major damage versus minor visible damage or no change.<br/><b>Google Maps:</b> <a href='https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp;query=10.432019875,-66.9625893625'>open</a>]]></description>
      <Point><coordinates>-66.9625893625,10.432019875,0</coordinates></Point>
