      <name>8. osm_way_233926035</name>
      <description><![CDATA[<b>Warning:</b> INTERNAL REVIEW ONLY. OpenStreetMap footprint candidate, not official EMS damage. VLM before/after output is a triage aid only; absence/presence here is not confirmation.<br/><b>VLM:</b> minor_visible_damage confidence 0.45<br/><b>Evidence:</b> Building footprint remains within the yellow OSM outline in the after image; rectangular mass is still discernible but roof texture appears altered with possible debris or partial roof disruption. Hazy atmospheric conditions in the post-event chip obscure fine detail.<br/><b>Uncertainty:</b> Significant atmospheric haze in the after chip limits confidence in detecting fine roof-level damage. The building mass is still visible, suggesting it did not collapse, but subtle damage (roof tiles, partial collapse, debris) cannot be confirmed. A clearer post-event capture would be needed to confirm or rule out major damage.<br/><b>Google Maps:</b> <a href='https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp;query=10.435098020000002,-66.9705091'>open</a>]]></description>
